track_notes: My first approach was to try to scramble up the SouthEast side of the  hill, but a rock wall stopped me.  I then dropped back down to the main trail and went around to a saddle, then up a rocky ridge.
This route is from the north trail head and takes trail #150 to the top

This is an optional loop you can do before you take the summit. This allows you to enjoy a longer hike to view the surrounding neighborhoods and the Phoenix area. 

The summit is a quick-steep scramble. Once on top there are many opportunities to set up an activation point.

This is a full and unstoppedtrack file taken from my Garmin.  Be sure to closely follow the signage.  some are not easily seen.  Slight scramble towards the top.  Also be on the lookout as some old, un-activated trails will take you away from the summit.
track_title: Short Route, Starting at TH 308 - 07/25/21 Activation
